{
  "texts": [
    "In a similar context, Nishio et al.",
    "39 employed transfer learning with CNN models pre-trained on large datasets to enhance the reliability and robustness of models trained on smaller datasets.",
    "The models they used included ResNet-50, VGG16, MobileNet, EfficientNet, and DenseNet-12.",
    "They specifically utilized the VGG16 model as a deep learning model for their proposed approach.",
    "Various data augmentation techniques, such as shifting, flipping, mixing up, rotating, random image cropping, and patching, were employed to compensate for the limited amount of data available and improve the model's performance."
  ]
}